io.amelia.looper

Class AbstractLooper<Q extends AbstractQueue>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.amelia.looper.AbstractLooper<Q>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultLooper, MainLooper

    public abstract class AbstractLooper<Q extends AbstractQueue>
extends java.lang.Object
    The Looper is intended to be interfaced by the thread that intends to execute tasks or oversee the process.

      • quitSafely

        public final void quitSafely()
        Quits the looper safely.

        Causes the joinLoop() method to terminate as soon as all remaining messages in the queue that are already due to be delivered have been handled. However pending delayed messages with due times in the future will not be delivered before the loop terminates.

      • quitUnsafe

        public final void quitUnsafe()
        Quits the looper.

        Causes the joinLoop() method to terminate without processing any more messages in the queue.

        Using this method may be unsafe because some messages may not be delivered before the looper terminates. Consider using quitSafely() instead to ensure that all pending work is completed in an orderly manner.

        See Also:
        quitSafely()
